<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-13T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="505" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10678: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-13T16:00:00+08:00">December 13, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>…There is no intimation as yet of reopening navigation on West River.
                            British gunboat <hi rend="italic">Sea Mew</hi> is now en route to Wuchow
                            with food supplies for foreigners, including Americans if needed.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>